New merge API examples

Start the server:

```sh
python3 qserver.py --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
```

Ask whether a project can merge now:

```sh
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/can-merge-now \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '"my-project"'
```

Possible responses:

```text
yes
```

```text
no
```

When the response is `yes`, the server creates `my-project.lock`. Future requests for
the same project return `no` until the lock is removed.

Tell the server the project is done merging:

```sh
curl -X POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/done-merging \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '"my-project"'
```

Response:

```text
ok
```

This removes `my-project.lock` if it exists. The server returns `ok` even if the lock
file was already missing.
